{"type":"user","uuid":"7ca859e5-0820-4226-b04b-0d36b2ed4015","session_id":"45bd4fe9-d12f-4930-90bb-1615d208ca29","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cdec0096b3af13573d1fe085b1a25","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: runtime\n   3→PATH: src/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/config.js\n  11→- src/http/server.js\n  12→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n  13→- src/services/chat-service.js\n  14→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  15→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  16→- src/services/audit-log-service.js\n  17→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n  18→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n  19→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n  20→- src/bot/telegram.js\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n  22→- src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n  23→- src/security/permission-guard.js\n  24→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n  25→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n  26→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  27→\n  28→SUBDIRS:\n  29→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n  30→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n  31→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n  32→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n  33→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n  34→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n  35→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n  36→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n  37→\n  38→INTERFACES:\n  39→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n  40→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, text message relay\n  41→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService\n  42→\n  43→TRAPS:\n  44→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n  45→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n  46→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n  47→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n  48→- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n  49→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n  50→- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n  51→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n  52→\n  53→DECISIONS:\n  54→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n  55→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n  56→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n  57→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n  58→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f006 | add security guard layer with permission tiers, param sanitization, confirmation flow, and audit logging\n  59→- 2026-03-14 | runtime-f007 | add test infrastructure with fixtures, helpers (mock-runner, mock-telegram, test-state, fixture-loader), and layered test execution (npm run test:unit, test:integration)\n  60→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cdebfd06760b7d02cd331bbc03246","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T21:14:14.336Z","_requestId":"831488a1f0e5461b9b01219ae792e61e"}
