ine-infra/` and `tests/services/`\n  29→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f001-user-stories.integration.test.js`\n  30→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm` and `.prizm-docs/pipeline/scripts.prizm`\n  31→\n  32→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  33→\n  34→- US-1: Unified config loading with readable validation errors\n  35→- US-2: Standard directory structure with Python/JS parity\n  36→- US-3: Unified script execution API (run/status/stop/logs/retry/reset)\n  37→- US-4: TypeScript and ESLint baseline established\n  38→\n  39→### Verification\n  40→\n  41→- `npm run typecheck`: 0 errors\n  42→- `npm run lint`: 0 warnings\n  43→- `npm test`: 29 tests pass\n  44→\n  45→---\n  46→\n  47→## F-002: Telegram Pipeline Command Router\n  48→\n  49→**Status:** completed  \n  50→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n  51→\n  52→### Deliverables\n  53→\n  54→- `src/bot/commands/index.js` - Router entry point (auth, parse, validate, dispatch)\n  55→- `src/bot/commands/parser.js` - Command parsing with alias support\n  56→- `src/bot/commands/registry.js` - Dynamic command registration\n  57→- `src/bot/commands/validator.js` - Parameter validation\n  58→- `src/bot/commands/formatter.js` - User-friendly error messages\n  59→- `src/bot/commands/help.js` - Dynamic help text generation\n  60→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Pipeline command handler\n  61→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/bugfix.js` - Bugfix shortcut handler\n  62→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/planner.js` - Planner pipeline handler\n  63→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Status query handler\n  64→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Logs query handler\n  65→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Stop pipeline handler\n  66→- Unit tests in `tests/bot/commands/`\n  67→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f002-command-router.integration.test.js`\n  68→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm`\n  69→\n  70→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n  71→\n  72→- US-1: Pipeline command with run/status/logs/stop subcommands\n  73→- US-2: Bugfix command as shortcut to `/pipeline run --type=bugfix`\n  74→- US-3: Status query showing all running pipelines\n  75→- US-4: Logs query with file fallback for large output\n  76→- US-5: Stop pipeline with confirmation\n  77→- US-6: Error guidance with clear suggestions\n  78→- US-7: Authorization guard on all commands\n  79→\n  80→### Commands Implemented\n  81→\n  82→| Command | Aliases | Description |\n  83→|---------|---------|-------------|\n  84→| `/pipeline` | `/p` | Manage pipelines (run/status/logs/stop) |\n  85→| `/bugfix` | `/b` | Start bugfix pipeline |\n  86→| `/planner` | — | Manage planner pipelines |\n  87→| `/status` | `/s` | Show running pipelines |\n  88→| `/logs` | `/l` | View pipeline logs |\n  89→| `/stop` | — | Stop running pipelines |\n  90→\n  91→### Verification\n  92→\n  93→- `npm test`: 105 tests pass (76 for F-002)\n  94→- Code review: PASS\n  95→- All 21 tasks completed\n  96→\n  97→---\n  98→\n  99→## F-003: Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion\n 100→\n 101→**Status:** completed  \n 102→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 103→\n 104→### Deliverables\n 105→\n 106→- `src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js` - Schema validation, version management, plan registry\n 107→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js` - Plan command handler (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n 108→- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Document upload handler for JSON files\n 109→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - Extended with resolvePlanListPath()\n 110→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Extended with plansDir config\n 111→- `plans/` directory structure with feature-list/ and bug-fix-list/ subdirectories\n 112→- Unit tests in `tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js`\n 113→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f003-plan-ingestion.integration.test.js`\n 114→\n 115→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 116→\n 117→- US-1: Upload Plan File - Telegram document message handling with auto-type detection\n 118→