ontroller.test.js`\n 157→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 158→\n 159→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 160→\n 161→- US-1: Unified Pipeline Start - startPipeline with daemon/foreground modes, lock acquisition\n 162→- US-2: Pipeline Stop - stopPipeline with ALREADY_STOPPED handling, lock release\n 163→- US-3: Target Retry - retryTarget with validation and mode support\n 164→- US-4: Run Single Feature - runSingle without lock (independent execution)\n 165→- US-5: Status Query - getStatus with daemon/pipeline state, lastResult\n 166→- US-6: Logs Query - getLogs with line limit, missing file handling\n 167→- US-7: Concurrency Protection - lock-manager with stale lock cleanup, forceUnlock\n 168→- US-8: Error Mapping - Consistent error codes with hint/context fields\n 169→- US-9: Telegram Handler Integration - All handlers updated to use pipeline-controller\n 170→\n 171→### Error Codes Added\n 172→\n 173→| Code | Description |\n 174→|------|-------------|\n 175→| LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED | Pipeline already running |\n 176→| ALREADY_STOPPED | Pipeline not running |\n 177→| PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING | No active pipeline |\n 178→| INVALID_TARGET | Missing or invalid target ID |\n 179→| TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE | Target state not retryable |\n 180→| DAEMON_START_FAILED | Failed to start daemon |\n 181→\n 182→### Key Decisions\n 183→\n 184→- D1: File lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (no external dependencies)\n 185→- D2: Separate lock-manager module for single responsibility\n 186→- D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n 187→- D4: New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service\n 188→- D5: runSingle does NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 189→\n 190→### Verification\n 191→\n 192→- Code review: PASS\n 193→- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 194→- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n 195→- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n 196→\n 197→---\n 198→\n 199→## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n 200→\n 201→**Status:** completed\n 202→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n 203→\n 204→### Deliverables\n 205→\n 206→- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates state from multiple sources for unified status view\n 207→- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with streaming support for large files\n 208→- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Telegram message pushing with throttling, chunking, heartbeat\n 209→- `src/services/index.js` - Exports all new services\n 210→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated with aggregated status and --type parameter\n 211→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated with pagination (--lines, --offset, --file)\n 212→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n 213→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle hooks (on/off/emit)\n 214→- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n 215→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n 216→\n 217→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 218→\n 219→- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status shows running/paused/completed/failed/idle state with progress\n 220→- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters (max 500 lines)\n 221→- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto-chunking at 4000 chars with [N/M] segment numbering\n 222→- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Event-driven heartbeat with 30s throttle\n 223→- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with log lines and duration\n 224→- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted state files\n 225→\n 226→### Commands Enhanced\n 227→\n 228→| Command | New Parameters | Description |\n 229→|---------|----------------|-------------|\n 230→| `/status` | `--type=feature\\|bugfix` | Aggregated pipeline status |\n 231→| `/logs` | `--lines=N --offset=N --type=feature\\|bugfix --file` | Paginated log viewing |\n 232→\n 233→### Error Codes Added\n 234→\n 235→| Code | Description |\n 236→|------|-------------|\n 237→| STATE_FILE_MISSING | State file not found |\n 238→| STATE_FILE_CORRUPTED | JSON parse error |\n 239→| LOG_FILE_MISSING | Log file not found |\n 240→| LOG_READ_ERROR | Log read failure |\n 241→| SEND_FAILED | Telegram send failure |\n 242→| FILE_SEND_FAILED | File send failure |\n 243→| HEARTBEAT_DISABLED | Heartbeat not enabled |\n 244→| INVALID_PIPELINE_TYPE | Invalid pipeline type |\n 245→\n 246→### Key Decisions\n 247→\n 248→- D1: Independent status-aggregator service (single responsibility)\n 249→- D2: In-memory message queue with retry (non-blocking)\n 250→- D3: CLI argument pagination (simple, no complex protocol)\n 251→- D4: Event-driven heartbeat + time throttle (30s minimum interval)\n 252→- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no additional storage)\n 253→- D6: Lifecycle hooks via EventEmitter in pipeline-controller\n 254→- D7: Message retry: max 3, exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s)\n 255→\n 256→### Verification\n 257→\n 258→- All 77 tasks completed\n 259→- Unit tests: 120+ passing\n 260→- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n 261→- NFR-1: Status aggregation < 200ms, log read < 300ms\n 262→- NFR-2: Push failures don't block pipeline (queue + retry)\n 263→- NFR-3: Test coverage > 85%\n 264→\n 265→---\n 266→\n 267→## F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n 268→\n 269→**Status:** completed\n 270→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 271→\n 272→### Deliverables\n 273→\n 274→- `src/security/permission-guard.js` - Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer) with env config\n 275→- `src/security/param-sanitizer.js` - Parameter sanitization with path traversal and shell injection protection\n 276→- `src/security/confirmation-manager.js` - Text-based confirmation flow with 60s timeout\n 277→- `src/security/guard.js` - Unified guard middleware for command handlers\n 278→- `src/security/system-guard.js` - System exec command guard with ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC control\n 279→- `src/security/index.js` - Module exports\n 280→- `src/services/audit-log-service.js` - JSON Lines audit logging with rotation (10MB/5 files)\n 281→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js` - /audit command for log query (admin-only)\n 282→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated with force-unlock, confirmation flow, audit logging\n 283→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated with confirmation flow\n 284→- `src/config.js` - Extended with security configuration\n 285→- `.env.example` - Updated with USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_* vars\n 286→- Unit tests in `tests/security/`\n 287→- Unit tests in `tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js`\n 288→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/security-flow.test.js`, `tests/integration/security-extended.test.js`\n 289→- Documentation in `.prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm`\n 290→\n 291→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 292→\n 293→- US-1: User Permission Levels - Three-tier model (admin/operator/viewer) with USER_PERMISSIONS env config\n 294→- US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization - stop/reset/force-unlock require admin, retry requires operator\n 295→- US-3: Parameter Sanitization - Path traversal, shell injection, and dangerous character protection\n 296→- US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions - Text-based CONFIRM with 60s timeout, --force for admin\n 297→- US-5: Audit Logging - JSON Lines format with rotation, query by user/time/action\n 298→\n 299→### High-Risk Command Matrix\n 300→\n 301→| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation |\n 302→|---------|---------------|--------------|\n 303→| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 304→| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 305→| `retry` | operator | No |\n 306→| `exec` | admin | No (ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC) |\n 307→| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) |\n 308→\n 309→### Key Decisions\n 310→\n 311→- D1: Three-tier permission model (admin/operator/viewer)\n 312→- D2: Text-based 